A top-performing track will occupy no more than 5% of the market, in which case:
 Digital score = 120,000*0.05 = 6,000

A top-selling album, however, can occupy > 80%, for which:
 Physical score = 10,000*0.8 = 8,000

Maximum digital score = 200,000*0.6 = 120,000 
 Maximum physical score = 200,000*0.05 = 10,000
